gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Celtics 124, Nets 114
gameRecap.excerpt: The Boston Celtics defeated the Brooklyn Nets, 124-114 tonight in Brooklyn. Jayson Tatum contributed a team-high 32 points to go with 11 rebounds and six three pointers, with Jaylen Brown adding an additional 23 points. Cam Thomas finished with a team-high 27 points along with 5 rebounds for the Nets. The Celtics improve their record to 5-0 with the win, while the Nets fall to 3-3 for the season.
